	<doc for="HtmlInputCheckBox.Checked">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets or sets a value indicating whether the <see cref="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlInputCheckBox"/>
is checked.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para><see langword="true"/> if
   the <see cref="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlInputCheckBox"/>
   control is
   checked; otherwise, <see langword="false"/>.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use this property to determine whether the <see cref="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlInputCheckBox"/> control is checked. This property
   can also be used to programmatically set the state of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlInputCheckBox"/> control.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para> The following example demonstrates a set of responses to users
